 and progress in deriving the quantum-corrected Newtonian\npotential. We will discuss how in quantum gravity theories linked to a\ngravitational path integral singularity resolution could be achieved by a\ndynamical suppression of singular configurations. Finally, we will show that --\nindependent of the specific ultraviolet completion of gravity -- asymptotic\nmodifications to Schwarzschild black holes are strongly constrained by the\nprinciple of least action at large distance scales.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Feb 2023 19:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 31 Mar 2023 16:36:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-03"}
