20consistent}. As a consequence of this, in a high dimensional\nsparse group selection problem, instead of using the so-called `gold standard'\nspike and slab prior, one can use the one-group global-local shrinkage priors\nwith polynomial tail to obtain similar results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Feb 2023 15:57:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-10"}
