{"id":"2302.10241","submitter":"Roland E. Allen","authors":"Roland E. Allen","title":"Some unresolved problems from a fresh perspective","comments":"67 pages. arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:1101.0586","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"physics.gen-ph hep-ph hep-th","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The many long-standing and still unresolved problems in fundamental physics\nand astronomy suggest that a completely new perspective is needed. Here we\nbegin with the simplest imaginable picture, and then progress, through a series\nof nontrivial arguments, to an action that contains the fields of the Standard\nModel embedded in a more complete theory, with $SO(10)$ grand unification,\nsupersymmetry (at some energy scale), and an extended Higgs sector. This last\nfeature predicts a novel dark matter WIMP with no interactions except\nsecond-order gauge couplings to $W$ and $Z$ bosons. Calculations and estimates\nof the relevant cross-sections for this particle demonstrate that (1) it may be\ndetectable within the next few years in direct-detection experiments (beginning\nwith LZ and XENONnT), (2) it may be observable within about 15 years at the\nhigh-luminosity LHC, and (3) there is a strong case that it may already have\nbeen detected in the gamma rays observed by Fermi-LAT and antiprotons observed\nby AMS-02. In addition to quantitative predictions for this dark matter\nparticle -- a mass of about 70 GeV/c$^2$, a current annihilation cross-section\ngiven by $\\langle \\sigma_{ann} v \\rangle \\approx 1.2 \\times 10^{-26} $\ncm$^3$/s, a collision cross-section for Xe nuclei estimated to be slightly\nabove $10^{-48}$ cm$^2$, and a cross-section for creation in a 14 TeV proton\ncollider estimated to be $\\sim 1$ femtobarn -- the present theory addresses\nsome other fundamental issues. These include the absence of an enormous\ncosmological constant, the thermodynamics of physical black holes, the\nregularization of quantum gravity near the Planck scale, a mechanism for\nsupersymmetry breaking, the origin of gravitational and gauge interactions, the\norigin of Lorentz invariance, the origin of spacetime coordinates, the origin\nof quantum fields, and the fact that spacetime is (3+1)-dimensional.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Feb 2023 23:31:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-22"}
{"id":"2302.10243","submitter":"Michael Glinsky","authors":"Michael E. Glinsky and Kathryn Maupin","title":"Mallat Scattering Transformation based surrogate for\n  MagnetoHydroDynamics","comments":"12 pages, 20 figures, 3 animations, accepted for publication in\n  Computational Mechanics","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":"SAND2023-12134 O","categories":"physics.plasm-ph cs.CE","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  A Machine and Deep Learning methodology is developed and applied to give a\nhigh fidelity, fast surrogate for 2D resistive MHD simulations of MagLIF\nimplosions. The resistive MHD code GORGON is used to generate an ensemble of\nimplosions with different liner aspect ratios, initial gas preheat temperatures\n(that is, different adiabats), and different liner perturbations. The liner\ndensity and magnetic field as functions of $x$, $y$, and $t$ were generated.\nThe Mallat Scattering Transformation (MST) is taken of the logarithm of both\nfields and a Principal Components Analysis is done on the logarithm of the MST\nof both fields. The fields are projected onto the PCA vectors and a small\nnumber of these PCA vector components are kept. Singular Value Decompositions\nof the cross correlation of the input parameters to the output logarithm of the\nMST of the fields, and of the cross correlation of the SVD vector components to\nthe PCA vector components are done. This allows the identification of the PCA\nvectors vis-a-vis the input parameters. Finally, a Multi Layer Perceptron\nneural network with ReLU activation and a simple three layer encoder/decoder\narchitecture is trained on this dataset to predict the PCA vector components of\nthe fields as a function of time. Details of the implosion, stagnation, and the\ndisassembly are well captured. Examination of the PCA vectors and a permutation\nimportance analysis of the MLP show definitive evidence of an inverse turbulent\ncascade into a dipole emergent behavior. The orientation of the dipole is set\nby the initial liner perturbation. The analysis is repeated with a version of\nthe MST which includes phase, called Wavelet Phase Harmonics (WPH). While WPH\ndo not give the physical insight of the MST, they can and are inverted to give\nfield configurations as a function of time, including field-to-field\ncorrelations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Feb 2023 22:03:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 22 Feb 2023 15:05:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-23"}
